item.title: How come no one can join my server?
item.dc:creator: @jmull jmull
item.description:
@jmull wrote:

[quote=“Al3x, post:9, topic:6024”]I found it and it says ‘Service Name’ ‘Server IP Adress’

 #  	Enable  	Service Name  	 Start Port  	 End Port  	Server IP Address
   Add Custom Service                  Edit Service         Delete Service[/quote]

add a custom service, then for start port and end port put “43594” for both. for IP address put the local address of your computer. If you cannot find this you can use a tool such as nettools4 to find it. it’s freeware so you can use it for later things that you might need to do.

you can get it here:
http://firstmilkman.com/stuff/Appz/appz/Net_Tools/NetTools4.0.171.zip

once you have downloaded and installed it, open it. once it is open hit Ctrl+a and it will tell you your ip on the local network. you cna then put this in the ip address info for your port forward.

you can of course totally skip this is you already know what your local IP is.

item.title: How come no one can join my server?
item.dc:creator: @jmull jmull
item.description:
@jmull wrote:

you will have to port forward on your router itself.

try using one of these ip’s in your internet explorer or firefox:
192.168.0.1
192.168.1.1
it will probably ask for a username and password, the most common of which are:
username:
admin
password:
nothing (not the word nothing but literally leave it blank) or “password”
